N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 9 ยง 5102.8 - False and misleading information

State Regulations

The commission may deny a license to any applicant
who: (a) supplies information to the
commission that is untrue or misleading as to a material fact; or
(b) fails to submit any statement or
information that would make any statement made in the application, in light of
the circumstances in which they were made, not misleading. Notes
